WEBVTT

00:03.504 --> 00:07.306
[mandy]

00:08.709 --> 00:12.111
I know, it's pretty different
without you in the wheelhouse.

00:13.547 --> 00:15.314
[sig] it would be fun
have you here, mandy.

00:16.050 --> 00:17.516
[mandy]

00:18.452 --> 00:19.518
[sig] uh...

00:20.388 --> 00:22.221
We started off slow.

00:22.223 --> 00:24.056
But I'm not giving up
on it yet.

00:25.926 --> 00:32.231
[mandy]

00:33.000 --> 00:34.433
[laughs] I know.

00:34.535 --> 00:37.836
Trust me,
I'm pushing as hard as I can.
That's all we can do.

00:37.905 --> 00:39.304
We'll get there.

00:39.306 --> 00:41.940
But we'll see it before
you know, all right?

00:42.343 --> 00:44.643
[mandy]

00:46.614 --> 00:49.415
[sig] it's really hard
to be here without the family.

00:50.317 --> 00:53.218
And... I miss 'em.

00:53.220 --> 00:55.521
But you know everybody
has to keep pushing.

00:57.658 --> 01:00.125
If you flinch when you're on
your heels,

01:00.127 --> 01:01.427
You can fail.

01:02.229 --> 01:03.462
[tobias]

01:04.465 --> 01:06.231
[sig] <i> 'cause what you do</i>
<i> when you're knocked down,</i>

01:08.035 --> 01:09.234
That defines you.

01:11.906 --> 01:13.205
Hang on.

01:13.207 --> 01:14.907
You just have to be able
to roll with the punches.

01:15.409 --> 01:16.508
[man] whoa!

01:17.311 --> 01:18.544
Uh oh!

01:18.612 --> 01:19.845
[keith]

01:22.316 --> 01:23.916
[all] whoa! Whoa!

01:23.918 --> 01:25.484
[bleep]

01:25.486 --> 01:27.319
Get him! Cut the line.

01:29.723 --> 01:31.723
[sig] <i> not everyone's gonna</i>
<i> make it.</i>

01:31.725 --> 01:33.025
There's no guarantee.

01:34.228 --> 01:35.427
But I wanna try.

01:47.608 --> 01:50.442
[narrator] <i> 3,800 miles</i>
<i> northwest of dutch harbor</i>

01:51.312 --> 01:52.444
<i> On the</i>  stalbas.

01:53.347 --> 01:54.913
[sig] okay, let's get going.

01:54.915 --> 01:56.048
Bags on the bow.

01:57.251 --> 01:59.551
Do it, right there.
Don't miss it.

02:02.423 --> 02:04.723
That's you.
That means throw it.

02:07.828 --> 02:09.828
Throw the [bleep] hook.

02:12.066 --> 02:13.632
<i> I know we're getting warm.</i>

02:13.734 --> 02:16.001
But uh, we wanna see
some real fishing.

02:16.804 --> 02:18.704
<i> Problem is time.</i>

02:18.706 --> 02:22.841
<i> Hopefully, we got enough</i>
<i> crab in the gear where we ca</i>
<i> come back in and offload.</i>

02:24.311 --> 02:27.045
[narrator] <i> just 48 hours awa</i>
<i> from his first delivery,</i>

02:27.114 --> 02:28.413
<i> Captain sig hansen</i>

02:28.415 --> 02:30.949
<i> Returns to his best sign</i>
<i> of life</i>

02:30.951 --> 02:33.519
<i> Betting the norwegian</i>
<i> red king crab</i>

02:33.521 --> 02:35.154
<i> Will make up for the loss</i>

02:35.222 --> 02:36.421
<i> Of the alaskan fishery.</i>

02:37.758 --> 02:39.591
If we could stay
on this momentum,

02:39.593 --> 02:41.226
I can make this payoff,

02:41.228 --> 02:43.061
Then make it back to alaska,

02:43.063 --> 02:44.129
Move on to the next one.

02:53.741 --> 02:55.541
[sig] <i> come on, come on.</i>

02:56.710 --> 02:57.843
Come on.

03:01.148 --> 03:02.214
[jarle]

03:04.151 --> 03:05.150
Oh!

03:08.722 --> 03:09.821
[bleep]

03:12.927 --> 03:14.126
<i> That's not looking good.</i>

03:19.233 --> 03:21.033
<i> See if you can't get</i>
<i> the second one up.</i>

03:23.938 --> 03:25.137
Start throwing it.

03:32.112 --> 03:34.313
-[man 1] oh!
-[man 2] [bleep]

03:37.218 --> 03:38.717
[sig] <i> oh, you're killing</i>
<i> me, guys!</i>

03:40.321 --> 03:41.420
Come on, man.

03:42.122 --> 03:43.622
Oh, please.

03:48.762 --> 03:50.262
<i> Come on!</i>

03:50.364 --> 03:52.464
Hey, stop [bleep] around.

03:55.202 --> 03:57.536
Oh, we got it.
We got it now. It's okay.

04:02.209 --> 04:03.709
[sig] <i> he's got one shot</i>
<i> at this.</i>

04:05.112 --> 04:06.111
Go!

04:07.047 --> 04:08.213
Go!

04:10.517 --> 04:13.051
Every pot is a nightmare.
Every single pot.

04:14.722 --> 04:16.054
<i> It's not that hard.</i>

04:16.123 --> 04:17.522
<i> A baby can do that.</i>

04:18.425 --> 04:20.225
My grandmother can do that.

04:22.029 --> 04:23.395
And she's dead.

04:24.865 --> 04:27.799
<i> Yeah, as soon as you see</i>
<i> the bag, you throw that hook</i>

04:27.801 --> 04:29.901
You don't wait for
it to go past the block.

04:29.903 --> 04:32.804
<i> I had the boat in reverse</i>
<i> and she still</i>
<i> didn't slow down.</i>

04:33.207 --> 04:34.306
It's a tank.

04:36.610 --> 04:38.310
We gotta get
him off the hook, okay?

04:41.849 --> 04:42.748
[jarle]

04:44.418 --> 04:45.417
[man] oh!

04:48.155 --> 04:49.321
Oh, man!

04:50.391 --> 04:51.423
Stop, stop, stop.

04:53.927 --> 04:55.227
Massive snarl.

05:06.807 --> 05:07.806
Guys, pull.

05:32.132 --> 05:33.832
Oh, come on!

05:46.947 --> 05:49.715
[sig] <i> these guys</i>
<i> aren't acting like they</i>
<i> belong on the water at all.</i>

05:50.751 --> 05:52.851
They're very discouraged
right now.

05:53.821 --> 05:57.055
But if you see some crab,
everything changes.

05:58.826 --> 06:00.525
<i> Bottom line is,</i>
<i> we need a new home.</i>

06:03.931 --> 06:05.364
[narrator] <i> 27 miles south..</i>

06:06.200 --> 06:07.399
<i> Inside the fjords...</i>

06:08.936 --> 06:12.037
Hey, so how're we gonna
mark these strings?

06:12.105 --> 06:14.706
[narrator] <i> ...On the fishin</i>
<i> vessel,</i>  tromstind...

06:14.708 --> 06:16.441
[bill] in case
anything happens
to the computer,

06:16.443 --> 06:19.411
Typically, I would right down
these positions so we can
come back and find it.

06:25.152 --> 06:26.952
Well, give me that pen
and paper plate.

06:33.427 --> 06:34.526
I'm gonna write it on here.

06:35.729 --> 06:38.263
Smells a little bit like
reindeer sausage so.

06:39.333 --> 06:40.632
I don't care,
this is all great.

06:43.036 --> 06:44.770
[bill] <i> with king crab closed</i>

06:44.772 --> 06:46.938
<i> I had no opportunity</i>
<i> to do anything right now.</i>

06:47.040 --> 06:48.907
<i> So, he asked if I wanted</i>
<i> to come over,</i>

06:48.909 --> 06:51.410
<i> And I mean, I jumped at</i>
<i> the chance.</i>

06:51.412 --> 06:53.512
We're definitely here to
put some money in the bank.

06:53.514 --> 06:57.249
I got a huge shipyard bill
that sucks!

06:57.350 --> 07:00.051
[narrator] <i> as sig tackles</i>
<i> the norwegian high seas...</i>

07:04.658 --> 07:06.758
[bill] <i> we're pretty much</i>
<i> fishing where</i>
<i> we're able to fish.</i>

07:08.128 --> 07:09.928
[narrator] <i> ...Captain</i>
<i> wild bill wichrowski</i>

07:09.930 --> 07:12.531
<i> Uses the 35 foot</i>  tromstind

07:12.533 --> 07:13.765
<i> To ply the fjords.</i>

07:14.701 --> 07:17.402
<i> Under sea valley's carved</i>
<i> by glaciers</i>

07:17.404 --> 07:20.038
<i> Over 2.5 million years ago.</i>

07:20.040 --> 07:22.707
<i> These steep banks</i>
<i> and jagged gullies</i>

07:22.709 --> 07:25.310
<i> Are overrun with</i>
<i> russian king crab.</i>

07:27.815 --> 07:29.614
<i> Dubbed stalin's red army,</i>

07:29.616 --> 07:32.851
<i> The invasive species</i>
<i> has no respect for borders,</i>

07:32.953 --> 07:35.954
<i> No qualms about destroying</i>
<i> local fishing gear</i>

07:35.956 --> 07:38.323
<i> And no cap on how many</i>
<i> can be caught.</i>

07:44.665 --> 07:46.398
Big one there.

07:50.504 --> 07:53.305
[bill] I've always been
an open water fisherman so
this is a little different,

07:53.307 --> 07:56.241
You know,
the tighter the fjord,
the faster the current runs.

07:57.711 --> 08:00.111
<i> With the current,</i>
<i> this boat gets pushed</i>
<i> all around.</i>

08:01.715 --> 08:03.648
[landon] <i> six strings</i>
<i> of five pots,</i>

08:03.717 --> 08:05.951
<i> All connected on</i>
<i> the same line.</i>

08:06.052 --> 08:07.419
<i> A little different</i>
<i> than we're used to.</i>

08:08.422 --> 08:09.721
Long line in for king crab.

08:11.124 --> 08:12.257
[bill] you guys ready?

08:13.827 --> 08:15.427
Come on, baby. Lots of crabs.

08:16.163 --> 08:17.229
Let her go.

08:17.831 --> 08:18.864
Letting her go!

08:22.302 --> 08:25.003
Okay, first mark, we're at 71,

08:25.305 --> 08:27.706
153, 6,

08:28.642 --> 08:31.977
25, 10.63.

08:36.617 --> 08:39.618
[bill] <i> supposedly some boat</i>
<i> have hooks that are coming u</i>
<i> with crab</i>

08:39.620 --> 08:41.953
<i> And they're fishing deep,</i>
<i> so...</i>

08:41.955 --> 08:45.123
We got it set within
the deep canyon
that runs all through here.

08:47.427 --> 08:49.628
We're further north
than we've fished in
the last trip,

08:49.630 --> 08:52.130
<i> So we have no idea</i>
<i> what to expect.</i>

08:52.132 --> 08:54.933
Timing's of the essence.
We need to get this gear
out and get it fishing.

08:55.502 --> 08:56.501
Clear!

08:57.938 --> 08:59.004
[bill] <i> see what this brings</i>

09:00.307 --> 09:02.140
[narrator] <i> 3,400 miles</i>
<i> southeast,</i>

09:04.845 --> 09:06.912
<i> On the alaskan bairdi ground</i>

09:09.316 --> 09:11.082
<i> Aboard</i>  the <i> wizard...</i>

09:13.020 --> 09:16.054
[keith] <i> I guess,</i>
<i> well obviously, the weather'</i>
<i> kicked up pretty good.</i>

09:16.122 --> 09:20.892
This next string, I'm gonna be
setting on a little bit of
a quartering course downwind.

09:20.894 --> 09:23.228
Just be aware of whoever's
on buoy is that, there,

09:23.230 --> 09:26.331
We will see some green water
trying to come sneaking
in on you.

09:28.335 --> 09:30.602
All right, pretty much
just about a mile, okay?

09:33.941 --> 09:36.675
Back is just, you know,
killing me, man.

09:36.677 --> 09:41.246
Well, my back'd be hurting,
too, if I was in the rack
for 12 hours straight.

09:41.348 --> 09:44.516
Rack duty! Who's on a rack
12 hours straight?
What are you talking about?

09:44.518 --> 09:47.118
[laughs] I think you ought to
get on deck

09:47.120 --> 09:48.720
Limber things up a little bit,
mouse.

09:51.158 --> 09:54.326
[keith] do a little
bering sea yoga, man.

09:54.328 --> 09:55.627
-Ah whatever!
-[laughs]

10:10.344 --> 10:12.210
Pretty gnarly.
I'm not gonna lie.

10:13.413 --> 10:16.114
Bairdi fishing is
a war of numbers so...

10:18.518 --> 10:21.419
Up north, where we've caught
a lot of crabs in the past.

10:24.257 --> 10:27.959
<i> I've spent the most money</i>
<i> ever going into a fishery</i>

10:27.961 --> 10:31.329
<i> That literally is</i>
<i> in a complete crisis.</i>

10:33.200 --> 10:35.000
I've got a lot of bills
to pay.

10:37.404 --> 10:39.437
[narrator] <i> delayed by</i>
<i> a costly shipyard,</i>

10:39.539 --> 10:42.974
<i> Captain keith colburn</i>
<i> bounces back from the loss</i>
<i> of reds,</i>

10:42.976 --> 10:44.109
<i> With bairdi.</i>

10:44.111 --> 10:46.745
<i> His plan, pay off his debts</i>

10:46.780 --> 10:47.946
<i> With crab.</i>

10:48.015 --> 10:50.849
<i> A million dollars' worth,</i>
<i> to be exact.</i>

10:50.917 --> 10:53.418
[keith] <i> this is not the way</i>
<i> to start at sea.</i>

10:53.420 --> 10:55.854
We've lost two of the best
deckhands in the fleet.

10:57.524 --> 10:59.090
<i> Tyler had a baby.</i>

10:59.092 --> 11:01.426
<i> His younger brother,</i>
<i> todd, retired.</i>

11:02.796 --> 11:05.130
And to replace that, I brought
three green horns on.

11:06.266 --> 11:08.700
<i> We're not running too far aw</i>
<i> from this weather.</i>

11:08.702 --> 11:10.402
<i> It's gonna be a little bit</i>
<i> dicey on this string.</i>

11:10.404 --> 11:12.137
<i> Especially, for these kids</i>
<i> out there, man.</i>

11:13.407 --> 11:14.406
[man] we're lovin' it.

11:15.709 --> 11:17.142
[keith]

11:45.105 --> 11:46.504
Y'all get ready
to brace yourselves

11:46.506 --> 11:48.206
'cause you will take
a splash or two.

11:49.042 --> 11:52.811
Ah! I hate sitting
on this course.

11:52.813 --> 11:55.747
<i> It's a slow enough set</i>
<i> that I can put</i>
<i> roddy at the rail.</i>

11:55.816 --> 11:57.849
But at the same time,
he's gonna kinda stay sharp.

12:02.956 --> 12:04.255
[keith] <i> whoa!</i>

12:04.324 --> 12:05.757
Hang on. Hang on.

12:08.829 --> 12:10.528
I'm shocked
you're still standing.

12:12.566 --> 12:13.631
<i> Good job.</i>

12:16.703 --> 12:18.203
[caleb]

12:18.705 --> 12:19.704
That's for sure.

12:22.309 --> 12:24.309
-Like I said...
-[laughs]

12:28.548 --> 12:31.549
[keith] <i> I really wanna get</i>
<i> this gear in the water</i>
<i> and get off this course.</i>

12:31.651 --> 12:33.084
But I don't have a choice.

12:33.086 --> 12:35.220
I mean, I either have to set
it like this or not set it
at all.

12:54.641 --> 12:56.608
All right, boys. Get it over.

13:04.351 --> 13:06.217
Cut it...
Cut the line. Cut the line.

13:10.657 --> 13:11.656
[narrator] <i> on</i>  the <i> wizar</i>

13:13.527 --> 13:15.160
[man] let's go, let's go.

13:21.835 --> 13:23.601
Cut it, soper!
Cut the line, cut the line.

13:24.237 --> 13:25.236
[bleep]

13:25.806 --> 13:27.505
[indistinct yelling]

13:27.507 --> 13:28.606
Is he clear?

13:35.749 --> 13:37.282
Let me get turned here.

13:41.655 --> 13:44.055
[narrator] <i> while</i>
<i> heaving the line</i>
<i> that connects the buoys</i>

13:44.124 --> 13:45.757
<i> To the 1,000 pound crab pot.</i>

13:47.360 --> 13:49.327
<i> ...29 year old roddy rodenba</i>

13:49.329 --> 13:51.062
<i> Tangles his foot</i>
<i> in the bite...</i>

13:51.631 --> 13:53.464
[bleep]

13:53.533 --> 13:55.500
[narrator] <i> ...Binding him</i>
<i> to the steel</i>

13:55.502 --> 13:57.235
<i> Plunging three feet</i>
<i> per second.</i>

13:57.304 --> 13:59.304
Cut the line. Cut the line.

13:59.306 --> 14:02.407
[narrator] <i> but</i>
<i> fast action from</i>
<i> deck boss gary soper</i>

14:02.409 --> 14:04.008
<i> Severs the green horn</i>

14:04.010 --> 14:05.610
<i> From his one-way ticket</i>

14:05.612 --> 14:07.512
<i> To davy jones' locker.</i>

14:07.514 --> 14:09.047
[keith] how's the kid doing?
Let me see.

14:09.148 --> 14:11.516
-He's all right.
-He's just laying
here for a second.

14:11.518 --> 14:13.384
You okay?

14:13.386 --> 14:15.854
Are you okay?
Or you just rattled?

14:18.225 --> 14:21.359
[keith] you got lucky, dude.
You got real lucky.

14:21.461 --> 14:23.728
I can't remember the last time
we actually cut a pot off.

14:24.664 --> 14:26.264
But you know the deal.

14:27.801 --> 14:30.201
Pots are cheap,
lives are irreplaceable.

14:51.358 --> 14:52.423
[bleep]

14:58.431 --> 15:00.064
I'm gonna get back
to work here.

15:01.902 --> 15:03.201
Let's go catch some crab.

15:05.705 --> 15:07.639
[narrator] <i> 3,400 miles</i>
<i> northwest</i>

15:09.509 --> 15:10.641
<i> On</i>  the <i> tromstind.</i>

15:23.056 --> 15:25.223
[bill] it's less than perfect
conditions today.

15:27.861 --> 15:30.061
You know we're in
the fjord so,

15:30.063 --> 15:32.563
With the amount of current
we have, these things
are stacked up

15:32.632 --> 15:34.933
One right next to the other.

15:35.001 --> 15:37.735
With any luck we'll get up,
try to find this bag,

15:37.804 --> 15:39.804
