And we all know that.

16:05.532 --> 16:06.531
[laughs]

16:12.238 --> 16:14.405
Came here to catch crab.

16:14.407 --> 16:16.341
No matter what
the weather is like.

16:17.043 --> 16:18.042
That's my guy.

16:24.918 --> 16:26.317
[bill] <i> this is all a prospec</i>

16:26.319 --> 16:28.252
<i> It's kind of a short soak</i>

16:28.354 --> 16:31.422
<i> To see if there's anything</i>
<i> really nice in this area.</i>

16:31.424 --> 16:34.225
I wanna see
what the first one brings.

16:36.563 --> 16:37.829
Come on. Get king crab.

16:40.700 --> 16:41.699
Come on, guys.

16:51.611 --> 16:53.044
[bill] king crab.
All right, baby.

16:55.348 --> 16:57.315
[bill] honestly, I'm glad
to see something crawling.

16:59.019 --> 17:01.052
This next one is

17:02.022 --> 17:03.221
A little deeper.

17:03.223 --> 17:04.255
Comin' up!

17:09.229 --> 17:11.162
Yeah, boy!

17:13.366 --> 17:14.499
That's good.

17:14.501 --> 17:15.500
There's some kings.

17:16.302 --> 17:17.568
There's some kings.

17:23.143 --> 17:25.410
[narrator] <i> after only</i>
<i> six hours of soak time,</i>

17:25.412 --> 17:28.246
<i> The string hits the crab</i>
<i> an hour threshold</i>

17:28.314 --> 17:31.716
<i> Opening the door to $50,000</i>
<i> a day</i>

17:31.718 --> 17:35.620
<i> And making bill</i>
<i> one of the only two</i>
<i> bering sea captains</i>

17:35.622 --> 17:38.056
<i> To catch red king this year</i>

17:38.058 --> 17:39.624
All right. Sounds good.

17:45.131 --> 17:46.130
Oh, yeah!

17:49.936 --> 17:51.602
-Looking good.
-Thanks, buddy.

17:52.806 --> 17:54.405
[bill] you know I should
probably give sig a call.

17:55.909 --> 17:57.008
[narrator] <i> 35 miles north.</i>

17:58.044 --> 17:59.310
[phone ringing]

18:01.047 --> 18:02.113
[phone ringing]

18:02.916 --> 18:04.215
[sig]

18:05.952 --> 18:07.218
[bill] hey,
what's going on, sig?

18:08.822 --> 18:10.321
[sig] <i> honestly, it's uh,</i>

18:10.323 --> 18:13.024
<i> It's not going as well as</i>
<i> I thought, that's for sure.</i>

